rComments: Takes 5 years to answer email's and doesn't give direct responses. She cuts class short, and yes I love a short class but not when you do not know what you are doing. She very unorganized, gives marks late (even after the exam.) She doesn't use good format or explain things well leaving you more confused than before. Want to say more but limited.
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: nice prof, but sucks at replying to emails. brightspace was a mess for her class. tries to hard too. just pick a different prof and stay away from here classes

Absolutely useless, got worse as the semester went on for the summer semester, classes were online and a month in she decided to no longer allow students to ask questions or have discussions during class, she would take 3 days to reply to emails and reply "yes!" even if it was a question asked.. easy class but she dosnt care for the students at all

I believe Professor Lee is a genuine nice person and tries, but her efforts are miss-placed. The powerpoint notes are some of the most disoragnized Ive seen in my four years at uOttawa. She is a very tough grader and provides no feedback. When you question why you got the grade you did, she is very rude. Group project area also a mess. Avoid

Easy course and very kind/understandable professor but gives surprise case studies/small projects and cancels class quite a bit. Study for quizzes they're fair but challenging (all practical no theory). Easy to pass with notes (online course) but doesn't provide them in class. Just keep track of upcoming case studies and you will get an A or A+

Ican't blv how she got such good rating. Her class is ok, prof has a good personality. BUT this is the POOREST organized course I have ever took after the 3 year in the university. On the website, notes is everywhere, she change class schedule for HER OWN CONVENIENCE, without respect student. Surprise assig will be given always, NO respect students

Her in-Class marketing case and project guidelines are incomprehensible because her English is bad. Then if you email her to clarify, she never responds. Her lecture notes are all over the place along with the class itself.
No complaints about Professor Lee, she is kind and accessible outside of class.

I love her! She was available for you and easy to interact with. Heavy reading and group work but generous grader for the group projects, we got A for both projects. Midterm was tough but the final exam was relatively easy- all M/C questions. Lots of examples during the class and she will ask them in the exam.

It was the best course I have taken at Telfer. Midterm was hard but it was fair. She is available for you to meet before/after the class and during her office hours. She cares her students but is a strict grader. Final was all MC which was pretty easy. I had an issue with group members though.
Amazing, prof just hard grader
Classes are pretty boring, not very engaging. She's pretty strict as well with grades and She can be so rude.

This was my first term in the university but I found this particular course is designed well to make me understand the expectations from the course. Attendance is not mandatory but I recommend you to attend the class that she shared the hint of the exam questions through out the class examples and discussions.

Powerpoints and notes are not clear and the exam questions are not relavant to what is taught in class as well unclear questions. She is hard to communicate with and does not answer questions asked by students in a proper way.

Im shocked she got such a good rating. Easily the worst prof Ive ever had in university. I had to send her a follow up email every time I emailed her to get a response. Lecture slides are all over the place, terribly done. When I went to speak to her for midterm review, she was laughing and joking the whole time. Ridiculous. Joke of a prof.

Absolutely love her, hands down best marketing prof! She is very kind and really tries her best to make the class engaging and make the material easy to understand. There is a lot of material to study and you need to add notes from the textbook to her course notes. The midterm was pretty fair & she is pretty clear about what you will be tested on

Such an amazing prof, she has weekly in class marketing labs but they're not worth much and are very easy (also marks them as pass/fail), her midterm had a little bit of everything so make sure to study key concepts and diagrams to do well in her class !!!

She is so understanding and accessible outside of class. She understands that group projects are tough so she's not so tough on grading those. Her lecture slides could be really empty sometimes, so just read the textbook and you'll get a good grade. Show up and do the labs to get the easy 10%. Overall, love her she is so kind.

rComments: Her lecture is engaging and fun, but I do not like the team assignment of the course. Some attendance pop quizzes during the class as well.
I really like her.
Nice prof
Her lectures are boring. Attendance is required. She is very kind and once boosted our project from C+ to B just because we asked her how we got that low. Tough grader tho.
Some of her explanations are unclear and the lectures are a bit messy, but she is a very nice professor and you can still have the ability to do well.
I really enjoyed her teaching and the class, being she is one of the nicest professors I've ever had at Telfer. Go to see her during her office hours.

Very helpful and a nice teacher.  Make sure to have the book or notes (notes from previous students should be good enough if you don't wanna put too much effort into it). Attend her lectures for participation marks.
She was always willing to help and was very understanding of any problems. A fair but tough marker, going to see her during her office hours, she will help you a lot.  I HATE group projects though.

A very sweet prof who really cares about her students! This class is pretty standardized which makes the final exam hard and the group projects suck! But she will help you a lot if you go to her office hours!
She was my favourite professor at Telfer. She cares about her students and really sweet.

Super sweet prof, love her as a person but would not take another class with her. She flew through the material and posted all of the slides but they were very disorganized and repetitive while not being overly clear. TOUGH marker on the group assignments, put in work. Overall if you study you'll know whats up.  videos she shows are hilarious!

She is very nice and cute. Three hours length lecture is not fun but she tries her best to make the dry subject matter fun. Attendance is mandatory, 5%. I would say her English is good enough to understand.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Group projects']

rComments: She's the nicest person and really cares about her students. However, her English isn't very good and her lectures are dry. Her class examples aren't very useful in helping you absorb the (lengthy amount of) material so be sure to study each week. Somewhat clear about expectations. Wished she spoke louder or used a mic.
She is a sweet person and really cares about each student and how they do. .
She tried to learn about her students and remember your name. Very sweet person.  Quiet heavy workloads, and 35% of teamwork.
She is very sweet and caring about students. I will recommend to anyone to take her class. I am not a big fan of the team projects though..
Such a nice Prof. Really cares about her students. Pay attention in class and know the slides well.

She is the sweetest person I have ever had the pleasure of having for a professor. I would recommend her to anyone in Telfer, and also to go to her office hours. She remembers everyone's names and tries her best to make the dry subject matter fun and interesting! But pick your group members wisely, they can make your life miserable.
